&gt; &gt; the way of morals, which means to understand, to acknowledge, to
&gt; devise, and to
&gt; &gt; act. It is not to be mixed up with religion, which means to
&gt; believe. However,
&gt; &gt; the two can be complementary. But they are independent one from the
&gt; other.
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt;
